cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with face age progression using a generative adversarial network (GAN) approach. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces an adversarial learning scheme, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves modeling intrinsic subject-specific characteristics, which can be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with photo-realistic facial details, which can be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves training a single generator and multiple parallel discriminators, which can be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
